<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 241<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary
                                            of State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                                            Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<hi rend="smallcaps">On Board
                                            the</hi> U. S. S. “<placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Augusta</hi>
                                        </placeName>”,] <lb/>
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-12">12 July
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>
                                    <gloss target="#t_MR1">MR</gloss>–<hi rend="smallcaps">in</hi>–35. Reference your <gloss target="#t_MR1">MR</gloss>-<hi rend="smallcaps">out</hi>-99 (State
                                    Department No. 16, 11 July).<note n="1" xml:id="d241fn1">
                                        <ref target="#d240">Document No. 240</ref>.</note> I concur
                                    with your recommendation and approve your suggested approach to
                                    the British Government.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>